1
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:14,667
<i>That's right, Olive,
don't be in such a hurry.</i>

2
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Slowly drive Emma insane.</i>

3
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:18,967
<i>- Dan!
- What?</i>

4
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:20,967
<i>Get out of there,
I need to use the bathroom.</i>

5
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:23,333
<i>Why didn't you use Mookie's
bathroom?</i>

6
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,667
<i> I have to pee!</i>

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,533
<i> Move!</i>

8
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:26,533
<i> Emma.</i>

9
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,500
<i>Why are you meddling
in our affairs?</i>

10
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>- Ouch!
- Mookie's getting hurt.</i>

11
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:31,467
<i> Jade won again!</i>

12
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:34,233
<i>Mookie wants to go to the school
she suggested!</i>

13
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:37,200
<i>Jade is not forcing us
to accept her help.</i>

14
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> We can kindly refuse.</i>

15
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,533
<i> She's pissing me off!</i>

16
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:42,767
<i>How come you're picking me up
today?</i>

17
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:45,567
<i> My mom might get mad again.</i>

18
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,000
<i> Look, Mom, this is for you.</i>

19
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:49,733
<i>We waited for you there,
but you didn't come.</i>

20
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,900
<i>Come here, don't go with
that woman ever again!</i>

21
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:54,167
<i> Emma, wait, what's the matter?</i>

22
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,000
<i> Stop!</i>

23
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,700
Mom, what's the matter with you?

24
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,867
Why are you so mad at Aunt Jade?

25
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,933
She's taking you away from me!

26
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:42,400
Just like how Olive took you
away.

27
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:45,233
Emma, I don't understand!

28
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:48,367
Where did all these crazy
accusations come from?

29
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,133
Come on.

30
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:50,633
Mom, what are you talking about?

31
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,133
I said let's go! Come on.

32
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:54,400
No, Mom.

33
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:58,133
I want an explanation because
I'm so confused right now.

34
00:01:58,267 --> 00:01:59,367
Let's go. Come on.

35
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,167
No, mommy, I can't breathe!

36
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,133
No, mom!

37
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:05,433
Mommy, you don't love me.

38
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:07,633
You don't love me...

39
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:09,967
No! Mommy!

40
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,567
What did you just call me?

41
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,900
Mommy?

42
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,467
I'm not Olive!

43
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,367
That's enough, Emma!

44
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,500
You're scaring her!

45
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:20,333
Why Mookie?

46
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:21,833
Do I frighten you?

47
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:26,767
Let's go, come on.

48
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:30,033
You don't want me anymore?

49
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:31,033
Why?

50
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:33,333
Because I can't give you
a nice home?

51
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:36,000
I can't afford to send you
to a prestigious school?

52
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:36,933
Is that it?

53
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:40,500
That's not what I need from you!

54
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:42,333
I'm still talking to you!

55
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:45,400
Emma.

56
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,433
Don't come near me!

57
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:49,600
Mookie!

58
00:02:54,933 --> 00:02:55,767
Mookie!

59
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:20,400
I didn't mean to call my mom,
Mommy.

60
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:23,433
When she dragged me

61
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:27,133
it reminded me of
how Mommy Olive treated me.

62
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:31,500
It's okay, Mookie.

63
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:33,400
I understand.

64
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:37,133
Well, the way I see it,
you didn't do anything wrong.

65
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:41,133
But Auntie, why is my mom being
like that?

66
00:03:41,267 --> 00:03:45,433
Why is she suddenly acting like
everything is wrong with me?

67
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:49,667
Does she have regrets about
having me?

68
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:54,133
Mookie, what makes you think
that?

69
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:57,333
Emma loves you very much.

70
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:00,833
Then why?

71
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:04,667
Then why is she acting
like she hates me?

72
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,733
I don't know.

73
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:09,800
Do you want me to talk to her?

74
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Emma...

75
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:32,233
Don't you know how to knock?

76
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:33,400
What?

77
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,933
But I knocked.

78
00:04:37,067 --> 00:04:38,367
Like this...

79
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,867
Didn't you hear it?

80
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,767
Do you think I'll ask you
if I heard you knock?

81
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:48,133
Sis, I knocked many times.

82
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,400
Why didn't I hear you knock?

83
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:59,367
Emma, are you okay?

84
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,533
I'm okay.

85
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,467
What wouldn't I be?

86
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:05,933
Okay.

87
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:09,467
I just came here
to check on you.

88
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,633
But if you say that you're
okay...

89
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:11,667
Then...

90
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,133
okay.

91
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:14,367
Bye.

92
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,267
I'll go ahead.

93
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:32,967
Dan, do you notice anything
different with Emma?

94
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:37,300
I noticed that she's been
irritable lately.

95
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:40,300
Perhaps she's just in
a bad mood.

96
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:45,267
Well, I hope it's nothing
serious.

97
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,133
Something serious?
What do you mean?

98
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:53,433
Nothing, I was just thinking...

99
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:57,100
Perhaps Emma needs to talk
to a psychiatrist?

100
00:05:57,233 --> 00:06:00,100
Maybe she's going through
something.

101
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:04,267
Or holding something in
that she can't tell you guys.

102
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:14,167
The food delivery is here.
Perfect.

103
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:20,400
I hope that this good food
can fix your mom's bad mood.

104
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:22,467
Come on, let's eat.
Let's go, Mookie.

105
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,300
Come on, Mookie.

106
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:28,067
I'll take your silence as a yes.

107
00:06:29,233 --> 00:06:32,000
Mookie, don't be like this.

108
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:34,800
You shouldn't avoid your mom

109
00:06:34,933 --> 00:06:37,700
just because you two
had an argument.

110
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:41,067
How will you fix things between
you two if you're avoiding her?

111
00:06:42,233 --> 00:06:44,133
Your Aunt Jade is right.

112
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:48,500
You guys can fix whatever
misunderstanding you two had.

113
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:52,000
I hope so.

114
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:57,433
I'm not used to having
an argument with my mom.

115
00:06:57,567 --> 00:06:59,933
It's only temporary.

116
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:02,833
I'm sure everything
will be okay.

117
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,033
Go fetch Emma.

118
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:09,433
We'll see you in
the dining area.

119
00:07:09,567 --> 00:07:10,600
Okay. Mookie.

120
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:16,600
Mookie, I know that
I'm not your mom.

121
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:21,400
But I want you to know
that I'm always here for you.

122
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:23,200
Okay?

123
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:26,200
Thank you, Aunt Jade.

124
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:28,233
Come on, let's eat.

125
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:33,400
The food is good. Let's go.
Let's eat, eat, eat!

126
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:39,367
Emma.

127
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,667
Emma, I was just talking
to Mookie and Jade.

128
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,733
What's the matter?

129
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,500
Why did you drag Mookie?

130
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:49,000
So Jade is putting her nose
where it doesn't belong again!

131
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:50,867
She said you've been acting
weird.

132
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Why are you taking her side?

133
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:55,000
You're just like Mookie.

134
00:07:55,133 --> 00:07:57,433
All you talk about is Jade,
Jade, Jade!

135
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:58,300
Emma!

136
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:01,033
We're just worried about you!

137
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:02,867
You don't need to worry
about me.

138
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,067
I'm fine!

139
00:08:04,667 --> 00:08:07,333
But the way you treat our
daughter is not okay.

140
00:08:07,467 --> 00:08:09,667
You know she's been going
through hardship,

141
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,833
and now you're hurting her.

142
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:13,167
That won't happen if Jade
didn't meddle.

143
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:14,367
Come on, Emma!

144
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,067
Jade helped us a lot,
and that's how you treat her.

145
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,767
What's the matter?
Are you jealous?

146
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,433
Because Mookie has a close
relationship with her.

147
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:24,333
What are you trying to say?
That I'm wrong?

148
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,233
Emma, you're being petty.

149
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:29,967
Jade just picked up Mookie
from school,

150
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,800
and you reacted that way.

151
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:36,433
After all we've been through
just to get our daughter back.

152
00:08:36,567 --> 00:08:38,300
And now you're hurting her?

153
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:43,300
I don't know what got into me.

154
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:49,133
You know what, Emma, I can't
deal with your moods anymore.

155
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,633
Are you trying to say that
I'm becoming like Olive?

156
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:58,200
No, I wouldn't compare you
to that woman!

157
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:02,100
You know what, come on,
let's eat.

158
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:04,033
Jade ordered some food.

159
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,100
Jade again!

160
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,400
Come on, you're just hungry.

161
00:09:09,767 --> 00:09:10,533
Come on.

162
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:12,033
I'm nothing like Olive!

163
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:37,067
Good morning, Emma.

164
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:45,000
Jade, I know that this is your
house.

165
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:48,400
But I need to talk to Mookie.

166
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:51,133
You know what, Emma?

167
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:55,300
I want you to patch things up
with Mookie.

168
00:10:56,667 --> 00:11:02,133
But she's not ready
to see you yet.

169
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:05,333
Are you trying to keep
me from my daughter?

170
00:11:05,467 --> 00:11:07,100
I'm her mother.

171
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,400
What?

172
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:11,533
Please, Emma.

173
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:14,600
It's too early for your drama.

174
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:18,733
You know, I just want
to protect Mookie.

175
00:11:18,867 --> 00:11:20,567
Because of what she told me.

176
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:25,700
Well, it's supposed
to be a secret.

177
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:29,100
But I think you need to know.

178
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:36,833
Sis, Mookie is afraid of you.

179
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:38,133
She said that?

180
00:11:39,367 --> 00:11:43,233
Well, because of what you did
to her.

181
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,967
We can't blame her, can we?

182
00:11:47,167 --> 00:11:48,400
I need to talk to her.

183
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:49,933
Hush now...

184
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:54,433
Emma, this is not the right
place and the right time.

185
00:11:55,233 --> 00:12:00,267
Mookie might get triggered
if you force her to talk to you.

186
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:03,733
I just want to apologize.

187
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:05,633
How about this?

188
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:09,467
Since it's Saturday today,

189
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:13,133
I'll take Mookie to a picnic
somewhere.

190
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:16,567
Somewhere quiet,
somewhere peaceful.

191
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:18,800
At least we're on neutral
grounds,

192
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:20,400
then you can talk to her.

193
00:12:20,533 --> 00:12:21,833
Does that sound good?

194
00:12:24,033 --> 00:12:26,433
You'll do that for us?

195
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:28,100
Of course, sis!

196
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:32,100
Anything for you!
That's what family is for.

197
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:37,800
And I want you to patch
things up with Mookie.

198
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:43,033
Go on, get ready.
I'll take care of everything.

199
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:47,733
Emma,

200
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,067
Leave her be for now, okay?

201
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,167
I'll take care of her.

202
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,600
See you!

203
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,633
Let's go!

204
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:22,267
There, this food looks good!

205
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:24,400
I'll take care of the rest.

206
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:26,733
Are you sure you got that, Dan?

207
00:13:26,867 --> 00:13:27,300
Yes.

208
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:28,500
Awesome!

209
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:39,733
Zayn, it's nice here, right?

210
00:13:39,867 --> 00:13:42,900
Yup, so beautiful.

211
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:54,367
You're right, Jade.

212
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:58,133
Mookie loves this place.

213
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,167
She seems happy.

214
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:04,867
Do you think we can work
things out between us?

215
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,367
Of course, Emma.

216
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,100
That's why I brought
you guys here.

217
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:14,400
So you can have a heart-to-heart
talk.

218
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,067
To make things right
between you two.

219
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,167
Thank you, Jade.

220
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:23,500
Mookie is the most important
person in my life.

221
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,167
I know.

222
00:14:36,567 --> 00:14:38,967
<i>That's why I'm taking her back.</i>

223
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,467
<i>I'm taking your husband away
from you.</i>

224
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:45,267
<i>And he won't even see
what's coming.</i>

225
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:50,033
<i>The way they'll see things,
you will ruin your own life.</i>

226
00:14:55,267 --> 00:14:56,500
By the way, guys,

227
00:14:58,233 --> 00:15:01,267
I brought mosquito patches
for all of us.

228
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:04,367
I'm sure there are a lot
of mosquitoes out here.

229
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:07,067
You know me, here you go,
Danilo.

230
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,867
Put that on you.

231
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,100
You can stick it on your clothes
or skin, it's up to you.

232
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,067
Here you go.

233
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,400
- Thank you, Auntie.
- This one's mine.

234
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:19,067
Emma.

235
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:22,733
Here, this is for you.

236
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:24,767
Put this on your upper arm.

237
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:25,833
No, thank you.

238
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,000
They can have that, I'm good.

239
00:15:27,133 --> 00:15:28,733
No, this one's for you.

240
00:15:28,867 --> 00:15:31,100
You never know what kind
of disease you might get

241
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:32,833
from mosquito bites.

242
00:15:35,133 --> 00:15:37,633
<i>Lunavaxil patches cause
hallucinations.</i>

243
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:43,033
<i> This is for you, Sis.</i>

244
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:45,833
<i>Let's push your paranoia
to the limit.</i>

245
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:48,500
<i> Who's the insane one?</i>

246
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:50,033
<i> It's you.</i>

247
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:52,900
<i>I'm taking you out
of the picture, Emma.</i>

248
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:56,467
<i>And I will take your role in
your husband's</i>

249
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,700
<i> and daughter's life.</i>

250
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,967
Will this work?

251
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,133
We'll find out.

252
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:04,433
Thank you.

253
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:05,367
Sure.

254
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:09,567
Wait, I'm gonna slice the
watermelon.

255
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,533
Mookie, dear.

256
00:16:11,667 --> 00:16:13,233
Do you want to eat now?

257
00:16:13,367 --> 00:16:14,400
I'll make you a plate.

258
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:21,167
Dan,

259
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:24,333
I'll be right back.

260
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:25,100
Okay.

261
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,200
That looks good, Dad.

262
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:35,567
It does, here I'll slice some up
for you.

263
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,067
Here you go, sweetie.

264
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,433
Thank you, Dad.

265
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:47,233
- Get some. Is it good?
- Okay.

266
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:49,100
It's sweet.

267
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:54,900
I'm sure mom will like this.

268
00:16:57,300 --> 00:17:00,233
Sweetie, I know how much you
miss your mom.

269
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:04,333
That's why I gave you some time
to think.

270
00:17:05,867 --> 00:17:08,500
I want to patch things up
with her.

271
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:13,967
That's why I came here,
so she and I can talk.

272
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:20,433
I still love her no matter what.

273
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:25,167
She's not like mommy Olive.

274
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:31,100
So I'm just waiting for
the right time to talk to her.

275
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:33,933
Okay, dear.

276
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,567
Excuse me.

277
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:55,367
Emma, are you okay?

278
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,800
Why did you bring us here?

279
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:06,233
So that you can spend time alone
with Mookie and talk to her.

280
00:18:06,367 --> 00:18:08,633
Are you ready to talk to her?

281
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:11,633
You keep asking the same thing?
Didn't I say I've been ready?

282
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:16,100
Okay, I think you're ready.

283
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:17,667
You talk too much!

284
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,733
Mookie!

285
00:18:21,867 --> 00:18:22,700
Mookie, baby girl.

286
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,100
Just put that down here.

287
00:18:27,233 --> 00:18:29,433
Your mom wants to talk to you.

288
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:33,433
It's good.

289
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,167
Emma.

290
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,233
Olive?

291
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:48,233
Why are you still alive?

292
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:59,800
Emma, it's me, Jade.

293
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:02,100
Olive is gone.

294
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:03,667
I will kill you!

295
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,167
Emma!

296
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,733
- Emma, stop!
- Help me, please!

297
00:19:06,867 --> 00:19:07,867
- What's going on?
- Help me!

298
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:13,200
Emma, stop it! Stop!

299
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:14,267
Emma.

300
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,567
What's going on with you?

301
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:17,967
Don't you see it? She's Olive!

302
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:19,233
What are you talking about?

303
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:22,533
What's going on with you, Emma?
It's me, Jade!

304
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:25,167
Emma!

305
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:27,200
Mookie?

306
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,633
Emma, why did you hurt our
daughter?

307
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,900
What have you done?

308
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:32,200
Why did you hurt Mookie?

309
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:33,733
Oh no, Mookie.

310
00:19:33,867 --> 00:19:36,233
Mookie, Mookie. I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to do that.

311
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:38,367
- Don't come near her!
- Mookie.

312
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,233
You're scaring her.

313
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,733
If you need help.
We will help you.

314
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:44,933
You need professional help!

315
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,033
You busybody!

316
00:19:47,167 --> 00:19:48,000
Emma!

317
00:19:48,133 --> 00:19:48,900
Emma.

318
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,200
Mom.

319
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:04,533
Emma!

320
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,033
Danilo, wait!

321
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:07,467
Your daughter needs you.

322
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,933
Mookie needs you.

323
00:20:09,067 --> 00:20:10,567
We need to bring her
to the hospital.

324
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:11,800
She might have a deep cut.

325
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:13,867
Okay. Come on, let's go.

326
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:17,167
- Zayn, stay here.
- Stay here for now.

327
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,167
We'll bring her to the hospital.

328
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:19,233
Come on.

329
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,933
<i> What have I done?</i>

330
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:54,300
<i>I don't know what's going on
with me.</i>

331
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,800
<i>I need to go back to my family.</i>

332
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:02,400
<i> Danilo, Mookie.</i>

333
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:16,033
<i> What got into me?</i>

334
00:21:16,167 --> 00:21:18,000
<i> Why did I hurt my daughter?</i>

335
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:19,600
<i> I need to go back to her.</i>

336
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,667
<i> I need to see Mookie.</i>

337
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:30,733
Well, obviously,
Emma is not in her right mind.

338
00:21:30,867 --> 00:21:35,200
She's not well. She hurt you.

339
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,500
What are you suggesting, Auntie?

340
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:39,500
Once we find Emma,

341
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:43,167
we should check her in a private
psychiatric clinic.

342
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:47,067
Are you willing to have her
confined to a psychiatric clinic

343
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,767
once we find her?

344
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,467
If that's what we should
do to help her, I will.

345
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,100
You have to find her.

346
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:55,567
Her again?

347
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:56,933
Where are you going?
